OL,6,FHer mum, Alison Parr, is her primary
OL,7,Fcarer and says the teenager, who
OL,8,Fcannot speak or write, was pursued by
OL,9,Fthe health service and threatened with
OL,10,Fa fine after she was prescribed new
OL,11,Fmedication.
OL,13,FAlison, a former A&E nurse, said
OL,14,Fbecause the wrong box was ticked on
OL,15,Fthe prescription she was asked to
OL,16,Fprove her daughter was disabled, or
OL,17,Fget Ruby to sign a letter giving her
OL,18,Fmum permission to respond for her.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/11
